The psychology of auctioning in excess: why spend more money?
At auctions the buyers are prone to spend more, to overestimate the goods.
Neurologists and research economists at the University of New York have been able to discover the neuro-economic foundations of this known and seemingly irrational behavior.
According to their study on Science magazine, men do not want to stay back in a race such as eBay auction, so they are available to pay even a higher price.
The research sought to trace the nervous pattern of this "lot" at the level of the nervous system through experimental auctions.
A group of volunteers played the lot, the other group of players participated in an auction while using the functional magnetic resonance method (fMRI) examined the active areas of the brain of the people participating in the experiment.
In both games the participants could win money, but in the auction game, in which the substantial element is to bid more than the other, the body striated under the cerebral cortex enters intensively into operation when you lose the game.
This brain area, in addition to other functions, plays a role in the "self-gratification" mechanism of the nervous system.
Therefore, according to the researchers, the rise of the price is explained by scanning the vehement reaction of the striated body.
To support their theory, the economists of the research group carried out a financial investigation.
In this survey, three groups tendered against a partner under different conditions.
The control group reported how much the actual value of the product in question was and they made their bet.
To another group besides this they promised that in the case of winning they would receive another prize of $15.
The third group would have received $15 before the auction, but the members of the group would have lost their money in case of a loss at the auction.
The difference between the two groups consisted of the fact that for one of them the win was emphasized, while for the other the loss.
By checking the hypothesis of neurologists the members of the group playing "against the loss" were willing to make higher bets than the control group or "winner".
"These results are not deductible from any of the previously existing economic theories.
These so far explained the phenomena that can be found at auctions with the joy of winning and avoiding risk.
Only the methods of creating the neurologic image helped to resolve the contradiction between the two theories, so that we came to a third explanation" - Andrew Schotter, professor of the Faculty of Economics of the University of New York, said.
Hepatitis: when to contact your doctor?
Almost half a billion people worldwide suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C, but in Hungary, chronic liver diseases are mentioned among the first causes of death.
In Hungary the number of hepatitis patients amounts to one hundred thousand, of which only 7,000 are treated: the reason is that many patients do not know how to be infected.
The definition of hepatitis is the collective name of infectious liver diseases caused by several viruses.
There are many similarities between the symptoms, typical are hepatitis and jaundice, but their pathogens and the diseases caused differ from one another.
Hepatitis viruses spread in two main forms depending on the pathogenic agent: hepatitis A and E through the food channel (e.g., water and food infected), hepatitis B, C, D and other viruses with blood and organic fluids (sperm, vaginal loss, saliva).
For travellers it is useful to vaccinate against A and B virus, against C there is no vaccine.
The symptoms of hepatitis A appear two to three weeks after the consumption of infected foods, accompanied by general malaise, weakness, abdominal pain and nausea.
After yellow spots are formed on the skin and on the white of the eyes, the faeces become clear and the urine dark, the healing takes place within two to three weeks.
A million people die every year for hepatitis B, the most serious variant of the disease, which causes liver cancer and liver cirrhosis.
The main reason is, according to estimates, that only one in ten person receives pharmacological treatment.
Hepatitis C can also have very serious consequences: if it is not treated it can cause liver cirrhosis and liver cancer.
Most infected people do not know that they have contracted the disease because pathogens subsidise liver cells, in many cases the first symptoms appear after 20-30 years.
Therefore, it is very important to prevent and carry out regular medical analysis.
This disease is much more frequent than the average in three groups: those who had a blood transfusion before 1991, drug addicts and tattoos.
In today's world, the number of people infected with chronic hepatitis C virus amounts to 200 million.
Because a routine laboratory examination also reveals that the disease is worth talking to your family doctor when you notice any symptoms of unknown origin.
Recognized in time the disease is curable, the virus can be eliminated from the body, thus ceases the infectious power and may be prevented from developing tumors.
September 30 is the World Hepatitis Day, first organized in 2004 by sick people's associations around the world.
The aim is to draw attention to chronic viral hepatitis, the causes of its development and the early recognition of the disease.
Who believes in God feels less pain?
According to the result of a recent survey, religious faith works as a kind of analgesic that has made the death of Catholic martyrs more bearable.
Scientists at the University of Oxford have conducted an interesting experiment, examining how faith in God influences the feeling of pain, the British Telegraph reported.
An electroshock of 12 Catholic believers and the same atheists was performed in the context of the somewhat bizarre survey, while all of them observed a painting depicting the Virgin Mary.
Based on the results, Catholic believers were able to reject much of the pain.
Thanks to the exploratory technique of the human brain it was discovered that Catholics were able to activate the part of the brain responsible for pain control.
The test is the first of a series of research in which in addition to academics also participate scientists, philosophers and theologians of the University.
The test was performed exactly like this: an instrument that emits discharges and passes the electroshock was connected to the left hand of the subject of the experiment.
The researchers asked the participants to focus on two paintings, the Virgin Mary painted in the 17th century by Sassoferrato and the Lady with the Hermelino by Leonardo da Vinci painted in the 15th century.
The authors of the examination hoped that the image of the Virgin Mary would give rise to a sort of religious state among believers, while Leonardo's picture was chosen because he did not differ too much from the other and considered it to be a reassuring effect.
The subjects of the experiment spent half an hour in front of the MRI scanner and in this space of time they received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive series, while they observed or painting on religious or other subjects.
The Catholics reported that the vision of the Virgin Mary made them feel "safe", as if "someone took care of them" and "they calmed down and were pervaded by peace".
Looking at the image on a religious theme, they realized 12% less pain than when they had Leonardo's work before them.
Psychologist Miguel Farias, who took part in the test himself, believes that such a result can be achieved with any image from the strong effect also for atheists, but you must find the right image.
"We need to look for an image to which they have very positive feelings, like a mother or a father," said the psychologist.
The Anglican bishop Tom Wright was pleased with the result of the research.
"The practice of faith should change, and in many cases can change our personality." - added Wright.
After the excellent results, only the question remains whether the painting of a Madonna of Leonardo or another painter of such a caliber is presented to the believers, what effect could it have on pain control?
Would the vision of a quality virgin Mary bring better results?
